\textbf{Problem 1:}
Starting from the odometer, you move around the ring by 9 steps in a clockwise direction. What will you find?

\textbf{Solution:}
When you move 9 steps in a clockwise direction from the odometer, you will end up at the Lhasa Apso.

\textbf{Problem 2:}
Starting from the odometer, you move around the ring by 10 steps in a counter-clockwise direction. What will you find?

\textbf{Solution:}
Moving 10 steps in a counter-clockwise direction from the odometer will lead you to the tiger.

\textbf{Problem 3:}
If you start from the odometer, move 9 steps in a clockwise direction, and then move 10 steps in a counter-clockwise direction, what will you find?

\textbf{Solution:}
Since moving 9 steps clockwise from the odometer leads to the Lhasa Apso and moving 10 steps counterclockwise from the odometer leads to the tiger, by combining these movements, you will end up at the Lhasa Apso.

Therefore, the final answer is: ``Lhasa Apso".

